issue.title: Fix Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) Bug
issue.body: # Fix CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) Bug on zakerias.com There is a noticeable **Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)** occurring on [zakerias.com](https://www.zakerias.com/) during page load. This causes elements (e.g., text, images, and layout containers) to move after they are initially rendered, which negatively impacts **user experience** and **Core Web Vitals** scores. --- ## Steps to Reproduce 1. Open [zakerias.com](https://www.zakerias.com/) in Chrome. 2. Open **Chrome DevTools** ‚Üí Lighthouse or Web Vitals extension. 3. Reload the page and observe layout shifts as fonts/images load. --- ## Expected Behavior The page layout should remain **stable** during loading with minimal or no CLS. --- ## Possible Causes - Images without explicit `width` and `height` attributes. - Web fonts loading late without `font-display` fallback. - Delayed CSS or JavaScript that alters layout after render. --- ## Suggested Fixes - Ensure all `` elements have `width` and `height` attributes (or use [`next/image`](https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next/image) in the Next.js version). - Add `font-display: swap` or `font-display: optional` for web fonts. - Reserve fixed space for dynamically loaded components. - Avoid inserting new content **above** existing content after initial load. --- ## Priority `Medium` ‚Äî Affects UX and SEO metrics.

## Description
This PR adds a utility script to quickly clear benchmark results and keep the project clean.

## Changes
- Added `clear_benchmark_results.sh` script that:
  - Clears all contents from `benchmark/results/` directory
  - Removes `benchmark/results_summary.csv` file
  - Provides user feedback on operations performed

## Usage
```bash
./clear_benchmark_results.sh
```

## Why is this needed?
The benchmark results can accumulate over time, taking up space. This script provides a quick and safe way to clean them up when needed.

issue.title: Excessive crop growth logging causes massive log spam in server console
issue.body:
**Description:**  
The mod prints **constant INFO-level logs** for every crop growth tick, flooding the console and `latest.log` with messages like:  

```plaintext
[Server thread/INFO] [cy.jdkdigital.productivefarming.ProductiveFarming/]: speed:12.5 growth:3 max:false state:Block{productivefarming:wheat}[age=5]
[Server thread/INFO] [cy.jdkdigital.productivefarming.ProductiveFarming/]: grow
```

**Impact:**  
- Log files grow **100MB+ per day** when automating crops  
- Makes real server issues harder to find  
- Wastes disk space and I/O  
- Impractical to share logs for debugging  

Would appreciate a way to control or reduce this logging. Thanks!

+"""End-to-end test for the agent data processing workflow."""
+
+import json
+import os
+import time
+import uuid
+from datetime import datetime, timezone
+
+from google.api_core import exceptions
+from google.cloud import bigquery, pubsub_v1
+
+PROJECT_ID = os.environ.get("GCP_PROJECT", "saigon-signals")
+TOPIC_ID = "dulce.agents"
+DATASET_ID = "dulce"
+TABLE_ID = "agent_runs"
+POLLING_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 60
+POLLING_INTERVAL_SECONDS = 5
+
+
+def generate_sample_payload() -> tuple[dict, str]:
+    """Generates a realistic sample agent event payload with a unique ID."""
+    event_id = str(uuid.uuid4())
+    payload = {
+        "event_id": event_id,
+        "agent_id": f"test_agent_{uuid.uuid4()}",
+        "session_id": f"test_session_{uuid.uuid4()}",
+        "timestamp": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
+        "event_type": "e2e_test_event",
+        "data": {"test_run_id": event_id, "source": "e2e_workflow.py"},
+    }
+    return payload, event_id
+
+
+def publish_event(
+    publisher_client: pubsub_v1.PublisherClient, topic_path: str, payload: dict
+) -> str:
+    """Publishes a single event to the specified Pub/Sub topic."""
+    data = json.dumps(payload).encode("utf-8")
+    future = publisher_client.publish(topic_path, data)
+    return future.result(timeout=30)
+
+
+def verify_event_in_bigquery(
+    bigquery_client: bigquery.Client, event_id: str, original_payload: dict
+) -> bool:
+    """Polls BigQuery to verify the event was processed and inserted correctly."""
+    query = """
+        SELECT event_id, agent_id, session_id, timestamp
+        FROM `{}.{}.{}`
+        WHERE event_id = @event_id
+        LIMIT 1
+    """.format(PROJECT_ID, DATASET_ID, TABLE_ID)
+    
+    job_config = bigquery.QueryJobConfig(
+        query_parameters=[
+            bigquery.ScalarQueryParameter("event_id", "STRING", event_id)
+        ]
+    )
+    
+    start_time = time.time()
+    while time.time() - start_time < POLLING_TIMEOUT_SECONDS:
+        try:
+            query_job = bigquery_client.query(query, job_config=job_config)
+            results = list(query_job.result(timeout=30))
+            
+            if results:
+                retrieved_row = dict(results[0])
+                original_timestamp = datetime.fromisoformat(original_payload["timestamp"])
+                retrieved_timestamp = retrieved_row["timestamp"].replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)
+                time_diff = abs((retrieved_timestamp - original_timestamp).total_seconds())
+                
+                return (
+                    retrieved_row["event_id"] == original_payload["event_id"]
+                    and retrieved_row["agent_id"] == original_payload["agent_id"]
+                    and retrieved_row["session_id"] == original_payload["session_id"]
+                    and time_diff < 2
+                )
+                
+        except exceptions.NotFound:
+            return False
+        except Exception:
+            pass
+            
+        time.sleep(POLLING_INTERVAL_SECONDS)
+    
+    return False
+
+
+def main():
+    """Main function to run the end-to-end agent workflow test."""
+    try:
+        publisher_client = pubsub_v1.PublisherClient()
+        bigquery_client = bigquery.Client(project=PROJECT_ID)
+        topic_path = publisher_client.topic_path(PROJECT_ID, TOPIC_ID)
+        
+        sample_payload, event_id = generate_sample_payload()
+        publish_event(publisher_client, topic_path, sample_payload)
+        
+        success = verify_event_in_bigquery(bigquery_client, event_id, sample_payload)
+        exit(0 if success else 1)
+        
+    except Exception:
+        exit(1)
comment.body:
![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

This broad `except Exception` block catches all potential errors during client initialization and test execution but immediately exits without logging any details about the error. This makes it difficult to diagnose failures. It would be more helpful to log the exception before exiting so the cause of the failure is visible in the CI logs.

```suggestion
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"E2E test failed with an exception: {e}")
        exit(1)
```
